android.support.v4.app

Interface ActionBar.TabListener

  • Enclosing class:
    ActionBar

    public static interface ActionBar.TabListener
    Callback interface invoked when a tab is focused, unfocused, added, or removed.

    • Method Detail

      • onTabReselected

        void onTabReselected(ActionBar.Tab tab,
                   FragmentTransaction ft)
        Called when a tab that is already selected is chosen again by the user. Some applications may use this action to return to the top level of a category.
        Parameters:
        tab - The tab that was reselected.
        ft - Unused, always null. Begin your own transaction by calling FragmentActivity.getSupportFragmentManager().

      • onTabSelected

        void onTabSelected(ActionBar.Tab tab,
                 FragmentTransaction ft)
        Called when a tab enters the selected state.
        Parameters:
        tab - The tab that was selected
        ft - Unused, always null. Begin your own transaction by calling FragmentActivity.getSupportFragmentManager().

      • onTabUnselected

        void onTabUnselected(ActionBar.Tab tab,
                   FragmentTransaction ft)
        Called when a tab exits the selected state.
        Parameters:
        tab - The tab that was unselected
        ft - Unused, always null. Begin your own transaction by calling FragmentActivity.getSupportFragmentManager().
